Say hello to our newest Citizen of the Week, <b>Kelly</b>!<br><br>Kelly lives at <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=ymca828"><a href='/home/?user=ymca828'>28229-C Main Street</a></a>, in Metro Park, and has been a citizen since April 24, 2007.<br><br>We salute Kelly for her ability to have fun: She was a top-scorer in Black Belt Karate, and has been trying to grow her trophy collection. Thus far, Kelly has 12 shiny trophies, including ones for Rope Race Master and the Peabody Park Cleanup&mdash;no surprise, considering she's a total outdoor enthusiast. In fact, her Millsberry pad has more outdoor space than indoor space!<br><br>Kelly has also attained perfect stats in fitness, civics, health, and intelligence. Way to go!<br><br>Pals say Kelly is friendly, creative, and smart. Her interests include reading, drawing, and playing the mandolin&mdash;all of which she practices outdoors.<br><br>So, when you see this sparkling citizen around town, be sure to say hello! She'll probably be sporting her British-flag dress!<br></div>
